Interface JTypeDecl

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JClassDeclaration

    interface JTypeDecl
    An interface supported by class (or later, interface) declarations.

    • Method Detail

      • declareThisType

        void declareThisType(Context context)
        Even before preAnalyze, declare this type in the parent context so that it is available in the preAnalyze method of other types.
        Parameters:
        context - the compilation unit context in which we're declaring types.

      • preAnalyze

        void preAnalyze(Context context)
        Pre-analyzes the members of this declaration in the parent context. Pre-analysis extends to the member headers (including method headers) but not into the bodies (if any).
        Parameters:
        context - the parent (compilation unit) context.
